Soa, 48 years old, is married and has two sons who are going to university. Her husband is a carpenter, and the couple lives in Tien Hoi village. For many years she has not only grown rice but also made bamboo brooms to sell. She makes a monthly income of about 3,000,000 VND. 
<p>
Since 2010 Soa has participated in SEDA. Previously, she borrowed 5,014,000 VND and repaid this loan punctually. Now she would like to borrow 7,194,000 VND to buy bamboo and other materials to make more brooms. 
<p>
Soa is the leader of a six-member group receiving a loan from SEDA. Besides Soa, the group includes:
Ly, 48 years old, who wants to borrow 7,194,000 VND to buy motorcycle parts for her store; 
Thanh (57 years old and the mother of two children) who wants to borrow 7,630,000 VND also to buy bamboo to make more brooms; 
Dung (45 years old and the mother of two children) who wants to borrow 6,758,000 VND to raise pigs; 
An (32 years old and the father of two children) who wants to borrow 7,194,000 VND to buy a computer; and 
Thanh (34 years old and the mother of two children) who wants to borrow 6,758,000 VND for her small business.
